Hyundai and Kia are currently streamlining all their platforms so the i10 is the first to use this all-new chassis, and then next-gen Kia Picanto will get the same one. The good news for both Kia and Hyundai is that it's a promising start, as the i10 is comfortable, with loads of grip. The steering is precise, the brakes are good. It doesn't even have any comedy lean in the corners. Which is all the usual journalist-speak for saying it's a very normal, and very competent, car.
